<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-06-17T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-06-17T04:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/3482: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-06-17T17:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">June 17,
                                        1924—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 17—8:15
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>185. My 176, June 13, 7 p.m. At conference of interested colleagues today
                            it was decided to approve proposal of consuls at Harbin with the
                            understanding that should future developments appear to make it
                            desirable we would order them to remove seals at once.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>